column1: #Summary1=(human1) This curriculum for Techtonica, a non-profit project offering hands on tech training, details a 15 week syllabus covering developer tools, webpages (HTML, CSS), JavaScript at React, Web APIs, databases, testing, data structures and algorithms, an Eventonica project and full stack practice, as well as a career week and assessments.

#Summary2=(claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022) Techtonica's free tech training program teaches full-stack web development using JavaScript over 15+ weeks, covering topics from developer tools and HTML/CSS to algorithms and career preparation, culminating in a final full-stack web application project.

#Summary3=(gpt4o) Techtonica offers a free, intensive, hands-on tech training program focused on full-stack web development with JavaScript, aimed at unemployed or underemployed individuals, emphasizing workplace readiness, self-directed learning, and project-based experiences to facilitate smooth transitions into software engineering careers.

#Summary4=(Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct) Techtonica is a free tech training and job placement program that provides intensive, hands-on full-stack web development training using JavaScript, with a focus on project-based learning and collaboration.

#Summary5=(Qwen2.5-3B-Instruct) Techtonica's free tech training program covers full-stack web development from JavaScript to databases and project work, preparing participants for the tech industry with hands-on experience and collaboration, culminating in a final full-stack web application project.
#Text=Techtonica is a non-profit project of SocialGood that does free tech training and job placement for unemployed or underemployed folks .
#Text=For more information , please see our website : Techtonica.org
#Text=Program participants will learn to do full - stack web development using JavaScript .
#Text=What bootcamps and Techtonica have in common is the fact that they are intensive training .
#Text=However , bootcamps can be pretty passive classroom learning and they cost $ 15,000 + for the students .

#Text=Techtonica aims to be more like the workplace to make the transition into the industry better — instead of having an instructor constantly guiding you ( which you wo n’t have in any software engineering job ) , you are given a general schedule of topics and assignments ( see our curriculum repo for an idea of the resources provided ) and you ’re expected to figure out what to do on your own or in collaboration with volunteers , mentors , tech groups , and other participants .
#Text=We ’re making Techtonica ’s program as hands - on and project - based as possible to best prepare you for work in tech .
#Text=The following is the approximate sequence of the topics during the program but is always being tuned and optimized so if you have questions , please open an issue .
#Text=Before beginning the program , participants meet weekly for 4 weeks to learn JavaScript fundamentals .
#Text=Participants should memorize common JavaScript built - in functions within the first month .
#Text=6. Intro to Command Line Interface Tools
#Text=20. One of either : Living in Open Workspaces or Working Remotely depending on program status .
#Text=7. Article : What Exactly is the DOM ?
#Text=8. How the Internet Works ( The Other Kind of Networking )
#Text=23. Deploy your Portfolio Project : Deploying Client - Side Apps with Netlify
#Text=7. Mini Project : Object Oriented Programming in JS
#Text=14. Install and Run PostgreSQL using Docker
#Text=1. Full - Stack Web App Using React and Express
#Text=1. Adding Tests to your NodeJS project
#Text=5. Testing React Components with Jest and React Testing Library
#Text=1. Deploying to Heroku with React and Node
#Text=2. Sprint Plan for Data Structures & Algorithms Week
#Text=4. Article by Techtonica Alum : Working in the field as a New Software Engineer out of Bootcamp
#Text=1. Intro to Security in Web Development
#Text=8. Final Project : Selecting Your Final Project
#Text=After Week 14 , Participants build a full - stack web application in the course of one month , from inception to production .
#Text=Creating project planning docs with wire frames
#Text=Planning out must - have features for their MVP
#Text=Updating status on their Trello board to meet weekly milestones / sprints
#Text=Gathering user feedback and adapting their remaining MVP plan
#Text=Recording a compelling demo for the finished product
